product.title: Haworthiopsis Tulista Pumila
product.description: It is an evergreen, winter-growing succulent plant with sharp succulent leaves arranged in rosettes of 20 cm in diameter.

product.title: Haworthia Truncata ex Sakai
product.description: In the wild, plants are often half-buried, leaving only the tips of the leaves visible above the soil.

product.title: Haworthia Atrofusca Watermelon
product.description: It grows in areas of summer rainfall and winter drought, in rocky soils at elevation where water drains sharply.
